---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About | francanete.dev" description="About the AI software lab behind francanete.dev.">
  <main>
    <section class="ed-wrap" style="padding-top:4rem;text-align:center;">
      <p class="ed-dept">Lab identity</p>
      <h1 class="ed-serif" style="font-size:clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4rem);margin:0.9rem 0 0.8rem;">About</h1>
      <p style="font-family:var(--ed-serif);font-style:italic;font-size:1.25rem;line-height:1.5;color:var(--ed-ink-2);max-width:48ch;margin:0 auto;">
        francanete.dev is an AI software lab that publishes research, experiments, and methods as part of its working practice.
      </p>
    </section>

    <article class="ed-read ed-prose" style="margin-top:3.5rem;padding-bottom:4rem;">
      <p>
        This site is not only a writing project. It is a lab surface for testing ideas, documenting results, and showing how AI-related software work is explored over time.
      </p>

      <h2>What the lab publishes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Articles that explain findings clearly.</li>
        <li>Experiments that test product, interface, and technical ideas.</li>
        <li>Methods that explain how the work is structured and evaluated.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why the structure matters</h2>
      <p>
        The site is intentionally organized so each page has a single purpose, stable links, visible metadata, and enough context for both humans and agents to understand the work quickly.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
